Why doesn't mac have the free command? despite sharing many unix tools, mac does prefer to do their own thing still and use their own separate tools sometimes
What can free do that vmstat cannot? free is more of a quick snapshot, while vmstat does dynamic observation of memory usage
What is disk caching? a memory feature which stores data that was recently accessed from a disk to a cache
What can free do that vmstat cannot? take more of a quick snapshot, whereas vmstat is dynamic, in other words, free is to vmstat kind of like ps is to top
How would I only display available memory output from free command? running: free -h | cut -c 1-7,40-50
How would I track my memory usage, update it every 2 seconds, repeated 5 times? running: free -s 2 -c 5
How do I only display total memory usage? running: free -h | grep Mem: | awk '{print $1, $2}'
